{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HA9oFBZJZTYkWCopAHxTLa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/14-dfda596/feedback.md`. Summary of findings:\n\n**LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS** — two compounding bugs:\n1. The title spans 4 lines; the algorithm caps joins at 3, so `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS` is never formed as a candidate.\n2. The best 3-line join (`LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA`) is then eliminated by the \"shorter wins\" dedup rule because `WITH NIGELLA` (a bare fragment) is a substring and wins on length.\n\n**Smażona zielona fasolka** — the bilingual detection guard didn't fire:\n- Polish mixed-case titles can't receive the structural heading bonus (+0.10 is all-caps only).\n- `GREEN BEANS BORKEUM` (all-caps translation on line 1) wins that bonus and outscores the true title.\n- The bilingual suppression logic requires cosine similarity > 0.4 between the two title forms, but Polish ↔ Korean romanization diverges enough in embedding space that the threshold isn't met.\n\n**Common themes:** all-caps structural bias over-powers mixed-case titles; the 3-line join ceiling; \"shorter wins\" dedup mis-firing on OCR fragments; and cross-lingual similarity thresholds being too strict."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1676,"cache_read_input_tokens":40117,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1676},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a7196b8c-4206-4b90-9bdc-acd6511dfbc5","uuid":"7166525b-c9c1-479f-98b9-71ba1ae743fe"}
